Subject: Publish docker image to ghcr.io/nadicodeai/argo

Replace upstream's Docker Hub publish flow with a GitHub Container
Registry publish so the image lands at ghcr.io/nadicodeai/argo. The
nadicodeai org does not own a Docker Hub namespace, and the upstream
workflow's `secrets.DOCKERHUB_USERNAME` / `DOCKERHUB_TOKEN` secrets
are not configured in this repo.

Why the image name is `argo`, not `argo-agent`: the new pristine-fork
repo (nadicodeai/argo) publishes a `argo` image. The legacy in-tree
rename repo (nadicodeai/argo-agent) used `…/argo-agent` because the
GitHub repo was named that way. We do not carry that legacy name
forward — see .shepherd/spec.md § Project Structure.

Auth uses the workflow's built-in GITHUB_TOKEN with `packages: write`,
so no secret setup is required. All four `docker/login-action` steps
across the four jobs (build-amd64, build-arm64, merge, move-latest)
are updated. The three inline `image=nousresearch/hermes-agent`
shell vars used by the :main and :latest ancestor-check logic are
likewise updated to `ghcr.io/nadicodeai/argo`. The `IMAGE_NAME`
env var carries the new value.

Note: the four `if: github.repository == 'NousResearch/hermes-agent'`
guards are intentionally not touched by this patch. The rename engine
maps `NousResearch/hermes-agent` → `nadicodeai/argo`, so they end up
correct in `dist/argo/` automatically.

Spec FR-7 (Docker image), FR-11 (Docker-only distribution).

